baseURI(uint256).details: Returns the base URI for a given tokenId. It return the base URI corresponding to the batch the tokenId belongs to.

params._tokenId: id of token to get URI for

constructor.details: Constructor is left empty and init is used instead

currentTheoricalMaxSupply().details: The max supply is calculated based on the current time and the mint interval, by subtracting      the elapsed_mint intervals from the initial max supply.      - The max supply is the initial max supply if the current time is less than the start date.      - The max supply is zero if the current time is greater than the end date.      - The max supply is decreased by one for each mint interval that has passed.      - The max supply is calculated by subtracting the intervals elapsed from the initial max supply.

encryptDecrypt(bytes,bytes).details: Encrypt/decrypt given `data` with `key`. Uses inline assembly.                  See: https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/69825/decrypt-message-on-chain

params.key: Secure key used by caller for encryption/decryption.

returns.result: Output after encryption/decryption of given data.

getBaseURICount().details: Each batch of tokens has an in ID and an associated `baseURIs`.                  See {batchIds}.

params._index: Index of the desired batch in batchIds array.

getRevealURI(uint256,bytes).details: Reveal encrypted base URI for `_batchId` with caller/admin's `_key` used for encryption.                      Reverts if there's no encrypted URI for `_batchId`.                      See {encryptDecrypt}.

params._batchId: ID of the batch for which URI is being revealed.
params._key: Secure key used by caller/admin for encryption of baseURI.

init(bytes).details: This function is called by the deployer/the factory when creating a contract

params.initPayload: abi encoded payload (CustomERC721Initializer struct) to use for contract initilaization

isAdmin(address).details: Getter for admin role associated with the contract to handle metadata

isEncryptedBatch(uint256).details: Returns `true` if `_batchId`'s base URI is encrypted.

params._batchId: ID of a batch of NFTs.

mintedPerAddress(address).details: Number of NFTs the user has minted per address

purchase(uint256).details: This allows the user to purchase/mint a edition at the given price in the contract.

params._index: The ID for the batch of delayed-reveal NFTs to reveal.
params._key: The key with which the base URI for the relevant batch of NFTs was encrypted.

saleDetails().details: Returns the sale details for the contract

setContractURI(string).details: Caller should be authorized to setup contractURI, e.g. contract admin.                  See {_canSetContractURI}.                  Emits {ContractURIUpdated Event}.

params._uri: keccak256 hash of the role. e.g. keccak256("TRANSFER_ROLE")

params.maxSalePurchasePerAddress: Max # of purchases (public) per address allowed

syncLazyMint().details: This function is called after the lazy mints has all been done in the init funcition.      It aligns the lazy mint storage with a new token ID by applying the chain-specific token ID prepend.

returns.chainPrepend: The chain prepend used to sync the lazy minting

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the URI for a given tokenId.

params._tokenId: id of token to get URI for

version().details: Used for contract versioning and validation

INITIAL_END_DATE().notice: Getter for the initial end date

INITIAL_MAX_SUPPLY().notice: Getter for the initial max supply

START_DATE().notice: Getter for the purchase start date

currentTheoricalMaxSupply().notice: Returns the theoretical maximum supply for the current time

getBaseURICount().notice: Returns the count of batches of NFTs.

getBatchIdAtIndex(uint256).notice: Returns the ID for the batch of tokens at the given index.

getNativePrice().notice: Convert USD price to current price in native Ether units

getRevealURI(uint256,bytes).notice: Returns revealed URI for a batch of NFTs.

init(bytes).notice: Used internally to initialize the contract instead of through a constructor

isEncryptedBatch(uint256).notice: Returns whether the relvant batch of NFTs is subject to a delayed reveal.

mintTo(address,uint256).notice: Minter account mints tokens to a recipient that has paid offchain

name().notice: Returns the name of the token through the holographer entrypoint

nextTokenIdToClaim().notice: The next token ID of the NFT that can be claimed.

nextTokenIdToMint().notice: The tokenId of the next NFT that will be minted / lazy minted.

reveal(uint256,bytes).notice: Lets an authorized address reveal a batch of delayed reveal NFTs.

setContractURI(string).notice: Lets a contract admin set the URI for contract-level metadata.

syncLazyMint().notice: Sync the lazy minting with the prepended tokenID

totalMinted().notice: Returns the total amount of tokens minted in the contract.

version().notice: Returns the version of the contract

withdraw().notice: This withdraws native tokens from the contract to the contract owner.
